I

IAlgorithm - Interface in fr.polytechtours.prd.multiagent
Interface Algorithm give the common methods for executing the different algorithms
To execute an algorithm, user should firstly load necessary parameters explicitly
Then user could begin with executing the algorithm
For certain methods, one object of data(with parameters) can give only one pareto solution
In order to get the pareto front, we should always call for the method generateParetoFront.

IEvaluate - Interface in fr.polytechtours.prd.multiagent

Individual - Class in fr.polytechtours.prd.multiagent.heuristic.meta
Individual to simulation one solution of NSGA2
One individual contains : genes: its genes of size N with 0 for scheduled and 1 for abandoned fitness: values of objective functions number dominated: the number of individuals which dominates this individual set dominant: set of individuals which this individual dominates crowdedDistance: crowded distance valid: if this individual is feasible or not

initGroup(ArrayList<Job>, int, int) - Method in class fr.polytechtours.prd.multiagent.heuristic.meta.NSGA2
Method to initialize the population
Here we use random strategy to initialize the genes of an individual: for jobs of agent A, choose randomly one job as scheduled.
initialWeight(ArrayList<Job>, double) - Method in class fr.polytechtours.prd.multiagent.exact.LinearCombination
Function to initial the weight for the jobs of agent A and agent B
Jobs of agent A are weighted with coefficient while jobs of agent B are weighted with 1-coefficient
